even if it's kept exposed to the sun.

154
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:19,540
It's the best for writing family
trees or drawing treasure maps.

155
00:09:19,540 --> 00:09:21,100
Paper airplanes, too?

156
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:21,890
Huh...?

157
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:24,030
That would be a waste...

158
00:09:25,300 --> 00:09:26,950
So how much is it?

159
00:09:26,950 --> 00:09:27,830
You're gonna buy it?!

160
00:09:27,830 --> 00:09:28,500
Of course!

161
00:09:29,020 --> 00:09:30,830
I caught her purchasing desire!

162
00:09:32,180 --> 00:09:34,880
I take it she's the type that price is
no object once she decides to buy.

163
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:38,490
Then, I'll just stir up her urge to buy as
much as possible and jack up the price.

164
00:09:39,050 --> 00:09:40,930
Even if you're interested...

165
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:44,870
