It's a secret.

220
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,000
That's not cute, you know...

221
00:12:11,370 --> 00:12:12,730
Leave it to me!

222
00:12:12,730 --> 00:12:16,560
I won't let anyone near you
until you're done with the work.

223
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:19,220
But... what if the wind direction
suddenly changes or something?

224
00:12:19,730 --> 00:12:21,170
Don't worry. Those clouds...

225
00:12:21,860 --> 00:12:23,740
If they don't move,

226
00:12:23,740 --> 00:12:26,140
we'll have a fine day today
and there'll be no problem.

227
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:30,320
Come get me only when something
changes with those clouds.

228
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:36,150
Let's see...

229
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,680
Things have been hectic

230
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:44,040
and I haven't had free time since
we entered the Grand Line, but...

231
00:12:46,180 --> 00:12:47,490
Little Garden...

232
00:12:48,210 --> 00:12:49,450
Drum Island...

233
00:12:50,430 --> 00:12:51,520
Alabasta...

234
00:12:53,010 --> 00:12:56,390
I've written down all
the routes that we took.

235
00:12:57,290 --> 00:13:01,840
I've stolen... no, obtained maps of the
surrounding areas from towns as well.

236
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:07,780
I'll draw... my own world map...

237
00:13:08,230 --> 00:13:10,170
my dream since childhood...!

238
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:27,560
Guys!

239
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:30,620
We'll make the deck spick-and-span
while Nami-san's working.

240
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,210
Okay!

241
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:33,580
Do your best!

242
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,170
You're gonna do it, too!

243
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,620
--You traitor!
--No fair!

244
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:41,640
--That's right!
--Then what about that woman?

245
00:13:42,040 --> 00:13:45,430
Don't be ridiculous! She's a lady!

246
00:13:45,730 --> 00:13:48,610
How stupid! It doesn't matter
if it's a man or woman...

247
00:13:48,610 --> 00:13:51,380
Just help us, Moss-Head monster!

248
00:13:52,030 --> 00:13:55,520
Ha ha, very funny,
Love-Love Machine goblin.

249
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:57,940
Just help us, or I'll beat
you up, you bastard.

250
00:13:57,940 --> 00:14:01,590
Go ahead. You think you
can beat the monster?

251
00:14:01,590 --> 00:14:05,010
You say that because you
don't know my goblin power.

252
00:14:05,010 --> 00:14:06,110
Oh, really...

253
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:18,220
I'll cut you down!

254
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:20,460
Want me to gut you?!

255
00:14:20,780 --> 00:14:23,220
I'll cut you into pieces!

256
00:14:23,220 --> 00:14:25,470
Go! Go! Fight! Fight!

257
00:14:25,470 --> 00:14:27,120
S-Stop it, both of you...

258
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:29,830
Usopp! Don't just stand there and
watch. Let's stop them already..

259
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:32,220
Don't be ridiculous!
Don't underestimate me!

260
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,810
You know there's no way I can stop them.

261
00:14:33,810 --> 00:14:34,690
Oh, yeah...

262
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,660
Didn't I tell you to be quiet?!

263
00:14:43,660 --> 00:14:44,570
Mellorine...

264
00:14:44,710 --> 00:14:46,560
J-Just one hit...

265
00:14:51,810 --> 00:14:53,120
For Pete's sake...

266
00:14:57,710 --> 00:14:59,750
Hey, Bellemere-san...

267
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:01,920
Bellemere-san!

268
00:15:05,860 --> 00:15:06,930
Bellemere-san...

269
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:07,630
Hm?

270
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:10,850
Say, where does the wind come from?

271
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:13,360
From the sea.

272
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,310
Sea?

273
00:15:14,420 --> 00:15:16,750
That's right. The wind born on the sea

274
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:19,270
brings blessings by blowing
on Cocoyashi Village.

275
00:15:19,590 --> 00:15:22,310
Not just wind. The rain, clouds, rainbows...

276
00:15:22,310 --> 00:15:24,740
Everything comes from the sea.

277
00:15:25,100 --> 00:15:26,800
I see... Say...

278
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,740
then where does the sea come from?

279
00:15:29,740 --> 00:15:30,980
--What?!
--Nami.

280
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:33,530
Don't give Bellemere-san such a hard time.

281
00:15:33,530 --> 00:15:34,690
But... Nojiko...

282
00:15:36,210 --> 00:15:38,160
Nami, you really are a curious girl.

283
00:15:41,370 --> 00:15:42,420
Nami...!

284
00:15:43,090 --> 00:15:44,510
Nami!

285
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:51,650
I heard you did it again!

286
00:15:51,870 --> 00:15:54,020
The lady at the bookshop
stormed into the house in a rage.

287
00:15:54,340 --> 00:15:57,280
Now, let's go home. The dinner is ready.

288
00:15:58,020 --> 00:15:59,520
Say, Bellemere-san...

289
00:16:00,260 --> 00:16:02,530
What's beyond that sea?

290
00:16:02,780 --> 00:16:04,200
Who knows?

291
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:08,240
I don't know what
lies beyond the Grand Line.

292
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,940
Even though you were a marine?

293
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:12,990
I was, but the sea is too big.

294
00:16:13,450 --> 00:16:16,760
I wanna see... what's beyond the sea...

295
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:17,780
Nami...

296
00:16:17,780 --> 00:16:20,960
I wonder if I can go beyond that sea...

297
00:16:21,340 --> 00:16:23,350
You're a strong child.

298
00:16:23,350 --> 00:16:25,930
If you really want, you can
go anywhere you want.

299
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,490
Then I've decided!

300
00:16:28,490 --> 00:16:32,160
I'm gonna use my navigation skills
to travel to all the world's oceans

301
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:35,500
and make a world map of everything I see.

302
00:16:36,660 --> 00:16:37,710
I sure will...!

303
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:40,850
That's right. I definitely will... some day...

304
00:16:41,450 --> 00:16:44,290
I will complete my own world map.

305
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:47,490
Hey, Luffy!

306
00:16:47,900 --> 00:16:49,320
Watch!

307
00:16:53,150 --> 00:16:54,610
Whoopie!

308
00:16:54,830 --> 00:16:55,830
Amazing!

309
00:16:56,270 --> 00:16:58,810
--Amazing! Amazing!
--Right?

310
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:01,000
Geez...!

311
00:17:02,370 --> 00:17:03,080
Ah...

312
00:17:03,450 --> 00:17:05,820
You've been working hard.
Are you done?

313
00:17:05,820 --> 00:17:07,960
No... But what is this?

314
00:17:08,370 --> 00:17:10,420
Hey, what're you guys doing?

315
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:11,890
Cleaning.

316
00:17:11,890 --> 00:17:14,130
This is pretty fun. Wanna do it, too, Nami?

317
00:17:14,830 --> 00:17:16,630
What's going on? It's noisy.

318
00:17:18,040 --> 00:17:20,560
What?! The Smooth Skin Soap?

319
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:22,390
Hey, it's dangerous.

320
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:25,000
It's okay! No problem!

321
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,280
Luffy!

322
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,330
That idiot!

323
00:17:32,330 --> 00:17:34,700
Gum-Gum...!

324
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:38,200
Bungee... Jump!

325
00:17:38,590 --> 00:17:39,740
Move away!

326
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:40,960
Watch out, Nami-san!

327
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:45,080
Are you okay, Nami-san?

328
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:47,970
Ah!

329
00:17:48,530 --> 00:17:49,960
Ow, ow, ow...

330
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:56,030
Ahh! My map...

331
00:17:56,030 --> 00:17:58,800
Oh, you were drawing a map?

332
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,170
What? Map?

333
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:02,270
So that's what your "work" was...

334
00:18:02,580 --> 00:18:03,860
That's right.

335
00:18:03,860 --> 00:18:07,130
It's the only map in the world
that recorded our journey

336
00:18:07,130 --> 00:18:09,430
after entering the Grand Line...

337
00:18:10,030 --> 00:18:11,230
And yet...!

338
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:17,120
My dream is to complete
my own world map!

339
00:18:20,290 --> 00:18:21,200
Leave!

340
00:18:21,760 --> 00:18:22,730
But...

341
00:18:22,730 --> 00:18:23,710
Just leave...

342
00:18:23,710 --> 00:18:24,370
Nami...!

343
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:25,620
What?!

344
00:18:25,910 --> 00:18:26,860
I'm sorry...

345
00:18:26,860 --> 00:18:29,010
If "sorry" were enough,
there'd be no need for the Navy!

346
00:18:29,010 --> 00:18:30,370
Now, leave already.

347
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:34,380
If you don't, you'll be fined 100,000 Berries!

348
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:38,640
It's your fault.

349
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:39,800
Why's that?!

350
00:18:40,070 --> 00:18:41,560
--Well, I think so, too.
--I think so, too.
--Seriously, those guys

351
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:44,440
--What?! You, too?!
--Now, Luffy, cheer up.
--always get in my way...

352
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:45,810
Hmm...

353
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:09,370
Hm? Smells like rain...

354
00:19:25,010 --> 00:19:28,640
There's a problem! Luffy! Luffy!

355
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:30,520
There's a problem! The clouds...!

356
00:19:31,130 --> 00:19:32,960
Spiders have ten legs.

357
00:19:33,620 --> 00:19:34,980
No, they have eight.

358
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:37,620
Hey, that doesn't matter! Wake up!

359
00:19:37,810 --> 00:19:40,320
--Centipedes have 100 legs...
--Usopp! Sanji!

360
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,780
Wake up! Zoro!

361
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:43,460
Someone!

362
00:19:43,920 --> 00:19:45,900
There's a problem!

363
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:47,450
Nami...!

364
00:19:48,450 --> 00:19:50,460
You'll be fined 100,000 Berries!

365
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:53,930
Wh... What should I do...?

366
00:19:59,210 --> 00:20:00,260
Done!

367
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,300
If I do say so myself, this is perfect!

368
00:20:04,030 --> 00:20:05,500
Am I a genius or what?

369
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,010
What?

370
00:20:08,370 --> 00:20:09,970
Hey, what happened?!

371
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:11,940
Nami!

372
00:20:12,220 --> 00:20:14,020
Hey! What were you doing?!

373
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:17,020
Why didn't you tell me
before it got this bad?!

374
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:23,250
Because... you said we'd
be fined 100,000 Berries...

375
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,290
You dummy...

376
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:30,050
Hey, you guys! How long are
you gonna keep sleeping?!

377
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,000
Ahh! What the heck is this?!

378
00:20:33,140 --> 00:20:36,010
--It's a tornado! It's a tornado!
--It's obvious!

379
00:20:36,720 --> 00:20:38,750
Luffy! Zoro! Fold the sails!

380
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:39,470
Okay!

381
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:43,060
Usopp! Chopper! Secure the
stuff on the deck using ropes!

382
00:20:43,060 --> 00:20:43,930
Got it!

383
00:20:44,210 --> 00:20:45,880
Sanji-kun! Turn to starboard!

384
00:20:49,060 --> 00:20:50,140
Umph!

385
00:20:50,940 --> 00:20:52,520
Point the bow of the ship
away from the tornado,

386
00:20:52,810 --> 00:20:53,870
or we're gonna get swallowed!

387
00:20:53,870 --> 00:20:54,570
Okay!

388
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:02,780
Hey, hey...

389
00:21:02,950 --> 00:21:03,730
Listen!

390
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:08,340
If my precious map gets washed
away by waves or something,

391
00:21:09,080 --> 00:21:11,000
you'll all pay...

392
00:21:12,060 --> 00:21:13,910
dearly.

393
00:21:14,770 --> 00:21:15,920
She really is scary...

394
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,720
The atmospheric pressure has risen
and the rain has stopped, too.

395
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:29,940
Thanks for your work. You can rest now!

396
00:21:30,290 --> 00:21:31,260
Okay!

397
00:21:31,260 --> 00:21:35,040
Well then, I'll go back to work,
so watch the clouds again.

398
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:36,180
You're not done yet?!

399
00:21:36,770 --> 00:21:38,110
Of course not!

400
00:21:38,350 --> 00:21:41,320
My goal is to draw up the world map.

401
00:21:41,620 --> 00:21:44,110
I've just finished the first one.

402
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:45,910
The real work starts from here.

403
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:47,370
She's really going at it...

404
00:21:47,560 --> 00:21:49,370
I like Nami-san that way, too!

405
00:21:49,590 --> 00:21:52,240
I wonder if there'll be a
100,000-Berry fine again...

406
00:21:52,530 --> 00:21:53,330
Probably...

407
00:21:56,080 --> 00:21:57,540
You've been reading all this time?

408
00:21:57,870 --> 00:21:59,750
Now, unfurl the sails!

409
00:22:00,130 --> 00:22:02,560
Full speed ahead!

410
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:04,310
Yeah!

411
00:22:04,310 --> 00:22:05,720
So, I'll leave the rest to you.

412
00:22:06,170 --> 00:22:07,200
Hey...

413
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:27,410
Which direction should I run towards
to see a more wonderful tomorrow?

414
00:22:27,410 --> 00:22:33,330
I took the helm and opened the
miraculous map that I stored in my heart

415
00:22:33,330 --> 00:22:39,590
I aimed for the sky and sought out
my dreams, though at times I got lost

416
00:22:39,590 --> 00:22:45,010
It wasn't a dream; when I met you,
I discovered the wonderful person in me

417
00:22:45,010 --> 00:22:51,270
With just a bit of courage,
I gained something grand

418
00:22:51,270 --> 00:22:56,690
Now's the time for my "wish"
to become my "pledge"

419
00:22:57,440 --> 00:23:00,420
Shining ray! Find your brand new way

420
00:23:00,420 --> 00:23:04,200
Let's sketch out the tale of the future

421
00:23:04,200 --> 00:23:09,460
I'll put all my feelings
in a brand new wind now

422
00:23:09,460 --> 00:23:12,450
Shining ray! Find your brand new way

423
00:23:12,450 --> 00:23:15,460
A never-ending journey to be together

424
00:23:15,460 --> 00:23:19,860
I'll chase after you
wherever you go, Shining ray

425
00:23:25,830 --> 00:23:28,330
Hey, do you know about the Navy's curry?

426
00:23:28,330 --> 00:23:29,190
Nope.

427
00:23:29,190 --> 00:23:30,050
It's famous.

428
00:23:30,050 --> 00:23:32,510
I hear that the chef on each ship
competes with all the others.

429
00:23:32,510 --> 00:23:34,100
Oh, yeah? That sounds yummy.

430
00:23:34,100 --> 00:23:38,200
The kid who fell from a Navy ship
earlier says he is a probationary cook.

431
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:40,570
It reminds me of my time
at the sea restaurant...

432
00:23:41,080 --> 00:23:42,480
On the next episode of One Piece!

433
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:45,780
"A Recipe Handed Down!
Sanji, the Iron Man of Curry"

434
00:23:45,780 --> 00:23:47,760
I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
